This paper proposes a novel pruning criterion for compressing deep convolutional neural networks, which is mainly related to computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) fields. The paper also discusses the successful application of the proposed method in a railway surveillance system, which indicates the potential relevance to artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE) fields. Additionally, the paper involves experiments on ImageNet, which is a popular dataset in multimedia (MM) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.MM.
